    explanation: 'Complete cytoreduction is defined as CC-0 (no visible residual) OR CC-1 (residual nodules <2.5 mm). The 2.5 mm threshold reflects the maximum depth of drug penetration from the peritoneal surface into tissue during HIPEC — nodules ≤2.5 mm can theoretically be eradicated by HIPEC drug penetration. CC-2 and CC-3 are "incomplete cytoreductions" and are associated with outcomes equivalent to systemic chemotherapy alone.',
